    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Overfitting Visualization</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;\n            background: #F5F7FA;\n            color: #333;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            display: flex;\n            align-items: center;\n            justify-content: center;\n            height: 100vh;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            transition: background-color 0.5s ease;\n        }\n        #container {\n            text-align: center;\n            border-radius: 15px;\n            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n            background: #FFFFFF;\n            padding: 40px;\n            width: 80%;\n            max-width: 600px;\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #5D5C6B;\n            font-size: 2.5em;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            transition: transform 0.3s;\n        }\n        p {\n            color: #7D7D7D;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            font-size: 1.2em;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n        }\n        .button {\n            background: #396AB0;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            padding: 15px 30px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            font-size: 1em;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.3s ease;\n        }\n        .button:hover {\n            background: #2B4A8A;\n            transform: scale(1.05);\n        }\n        #scatter-plot {\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 300px;\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            position: relative;\n            background: linear-gradient(to right, #E4E4E9, #A2A2C8);\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            overflow: hidden;\n        }\n        .point {\n            position: absolute;\n            border-radius: 50%;\n            background: #FFA500;\n            transition: transform 0.3s;\n        }\n        .curve {\n            position: absolute;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.2);\n            clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 100%, 0 100%);\n            transition: clip-path 0.3s;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<div id=\"container\">\n    <h1>Understanding Overfitting</h1>\n    <p>Overfitting occurs when a model learns the noise in the training data, leading to less effective predictions on new data.</p>\n    \n    <div id=\"scatter-plot\">\n        <div class=\"curve\" id=\"curve\"></div>\n        <div class=\"point\" style=\"width: 10px; height: 10px; left: 20%; top: 40%;\"></div>\n        <div class=\"point\" style=\"width: 12px; height: 12px; left: 50%; top: 30%;\"></div>\n        <div class=\"point\" style=\"width: 8px; height: 8px; left: 70%; top: 60%;\"></div>\n        <div class=\"point\" style=\"width: 11px; height: 11px; left: 30%; top: 70%;\"></div>\n        <div class=\"point\" style=\"width: 9px; height: 9px; left: 10%; top: 80%;\"></div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <button class=\"button\" onclick=\"toggleAnimation()\">Animate</button>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n    let animating = false;\n    function toggleAnimation() {\n        animating = !animating;\n        const points = document.querySelectorAll('.point');\n        if (animating) {\n            points.forEach(point => {\n                point.style.transition = \"transform 0.5s\";\n                point.style.transform = `translateY(-15px)`;\n            });\n            document.getElementById('curve').style.clipPath = \"polygon(0 80%, 25% 60%, 50% 90%, 75% 20%, 100% 60%, 100% 100%, 0 100%)\";\n        } else {\n            points.forEach(point => {\n                point.style.transform = `translateY(0)`;\n            });\n            document.getElementById('curve').style.clipPath = \"polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 100%, 0 100%)\";\n        }\n    }\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
